Testing

1. Add testing libraries to project's Gemfile
  * teaspoon  (testing framework)
  * phantomjs (headless web client)


2. Install Istanbul with npm (code coverage)
  * npm install -g istanbul

3. Generate stuff
  rails generate teaspoon:install --framework=jasmine --coffee

4. CLI
  bundle exec teaspoon




Files You Should Know About

config/initializers/teaspoon.rb
spec/javascripts/spec_helper.coffee



# Turn on teaspoon-guard
bundle exec guard start






###
CAPYBARA TESTING
###
--> restore production database to myapp_test
--> DON'T run rake db:migrate or db:test:prepare
